To divide \(\tfrac{2}{5}\) by \(-10\), rewrite \(-10\) as a fraction and multiply:

\[
\frac{2}{5}\div(-10)
= \frac{2}{5}\times\frac{1}{-10}
= \frac{2\cdot1}{5\cdot(-10)}
= \frac{2}{-50}
= -\frac{1}{25}.
\]

To compute 

\[
\frac{11}{2}\;\div\;\frac{7}{8}\;\times\;\frac{2}{11},
\]

follow these steps:

1. Division by a fraction means multiplying by its reciprocal:
   \[
   \frac{11}{2}\;\div\;\frac{7}{8}
   = \frac{11}{2}\;\times\;\frac{8}{7}
   = \frac{11\cdot 8}{2\cdot 7}
   = \frac{88}{14}
   = \frac{44}{7}.
   \]

2. Now multiply by \(\tfrac{2}{11}\):
   \[
   \frac{44}{7}\;\times\;\frac{2}{11}
   = \frac{44\cdot 2}{7\cdot 11}
   = \frac{88}{77}
   = \frac{8}{7}.
   \]

So the simplified result is \(\displaystyle \frac{8}{7}.\)
